 Fire &amp; Cold. Especially I think that lure of flames worked well. There was no mobs that can resist my lure spells. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Hmm, though my FR is 100 without buff and CR is just 80. I resisted AE spells many times. If you can find a way to avoid its cruel AE spells. Your groups can do HoT easily I think.<br><br>Just try it.<br><br><br><br>Yulle Icevale<br><br>ps. BTW, I think that HoT is good place for farming plate pieces. During 2 days, I just saw just one INT caster piece. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://yulle.mpogfan.com" target="_blank"><IMG SRC="http://yulle.mpogfan.com/cgi/zboard/data/yulle_sign3.jpg" border=0></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/upentagarnmanastorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pentagarn Manastorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/31/01 7:32:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What lvl is Hall of Testing?</span><hr size=1> 55+ is highly recommended.  Below 52, even with great resists, you just die from AE.  Having a couple high level warriors to control agro is good.<br><br>Recommend 150 self buffed resists (Elemental Armor) to avoid most of the damage.  At 55, resisted enough to keep epic effect on the entire fight.  Get a local druid to circle summer/winter to get them to 200/200.<br><br>Both lures help a lot.  At 55, fire draught hits well most of the time.  Magic spells do not fair well against these mobs.  Basically red mobs hit with cold, white mobs hit with fire, everything else is fielders choice.  The green mobs seen to be slightly more resistant to fire, grey mobs slightly more resistant to ice.<br><br>Been there about 6 times.  2 silk robes, 4 silk boots, 3 silk gloves, couple of halo's, 7 pair of pants, some sleeves and bracers that we usually leave to rot.  For wizards, the gloves, pants and boots are worthwhile.  The robe is nice, but not that much nicer than a sorcerer robe/sage robe to consider getting gems for.  Sleeves are good for mana and I dont know anyone that would give up carmine turbin/frog crown to wear the circlet on a regular basis.  So silk can drop, but it is very hit or miss.  Sometimes it is nothing but plate, sometimes nothing but silk.<br><br>Pentagarn Manastorm<br>55 Evoker of the Royal Norrathian Guard<br>Tribunal<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarkarius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arkarius </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/20/01 2:56:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What lvl is Hall of Testing?</span><hr size=1> 2 silk robes in 6 times? damn your lucky... been there probably 50ish times and guild only as 3 robes.. 1 of which ebayed and went to the giant guild on the server and the other went inactive hehe. Oh well we'll be moving to north wing soon enough. <p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Profile=0&Id=18002">Arkarius Angelwing <br></a>58th Evoker <br><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=89819">Lizardaman Scalekeeper<br></a>47th SK<br><b><a  href="http://www.tidesofdestiny.com">Tides of Destiny</a> <br> </b