lass=title> Re: What lvl is Hall of Testing?</span><hr size=1> Pentagarn you ever heard of MQ???? hell loot the arms and bracers and sell them on the market... nice way to make money..<br><br>Yilar<br>57 Evoker<br>MM <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaroob.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daroob</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/6/01 7:18:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What lvl is Hall of Testing?</span><hr size=1> I've seen lots of posts suggesting 55+, but I've been in HoT and been quite effective at 54.  Cold resist is the only one I would suggest you improve, and even then unbuffed 100 seems like overkill.  Mine isn't nearly so high.<br><br>Lure works quite well, and generally either draught of fire or jiva will also be effective.<br><br>The thing to remember is to not stand around taking AE's.  Unhide, nuke, hide, repeat.  You shouldn't get hit by more than one 300pt AE if you learn your timing.<br><br>The only exceptions are white dragons.  At the end of these fights I find myself having to endure AEs as I chain nuke to prevent gating.  Marginally cold resist + Druid Circle + Cleric Aegoism has consistently kept me alive. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubaedm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baedm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/3/02 12:01:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What lvl is Hall of Testing?</span><hr size=1> I started going when I was lvl 55.  I had to use lures, because nothing else will hit reliably.  Hide + Nuke is a MUST.  Even if you have 150 resists unbuffed, that AE can smoke you fast. <p><BR><A HREF="mailto:baedm@hotmail.com">Baedm Solarrain</A><BR><A HREF="http://pages.infinit.net/adorno">Order of the Scattered Winds</A><BR><A HREF="http://www.berthall.com">Bertoxxulous</A><BR><i>My Mamma always said," N00b is as N00b does."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uobiquon1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Obiquon1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/6/02 8:48:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What lvl is Hall of Testing?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> HoT.. um I would say if you under 57 don't even think of going there.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>I started going there at 55. use lure or frost/flame on the wurms and draughts on the drake/butterflies. You'll do just fine. however, get your resists up (poison/fire/cold).<br><br> <p><br><br><center><img src="http://www.magicalcheese.com/uploads/obiquon/obisig2.jpg"><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68512" target="_blank">[ I got a bad feeling about this ]</a> <br></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ualikatastrae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alikat Astrae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.attbi.com/~denu5/ali.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/10/02 6:05:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~denu5/ali2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What lvl is Hall of Testing?</span><hr size=1> Hmmm... I'm a 54 Wizard, got unbuffed CR, FR, and MR around 70, and I go to the Halls of Testing once a week and have a great time.  You need to use tactics, hug the wall to avoid the AoE's unless you've run out to nuke, and buff up like a maniac beforehand with both your own and other player's buffs.  It's great to have a Druid along to cast Circles of Summer and Winter, and Aegolism is really useful (bring a few peridots to give a Cleric for that) can really help out.  <br><br>You of course will have to be healed and/or regenerated for each pull, but with your DD spells you'll be pulling your weight, these things have incredible hitpoints, hit hard as heck, and therefore they are really rough on the main tank and healer, so anything that can shorten the fight is good.  This is one of the few dungeons where I'm almost always at full mana during the pull (because of the exhausted clerics), it's my hitpoints I have to watch like a hawk.  <br><br>Bind outside the Temple at the zone in and you can gate out if there's noplace to escape the aoe, and come back into the HoT when it's safe to open the door from the Hub.  I don't recommend even thinking about ToV until you have done enough raiding in Kael Drakkel to be allied to Claws of Veeshan faction, but I enjoy it at 54 immensely and these SS boots, bracer, and circlet make me feel all high level and stuff.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p>Alikat Astrae, Level 54 Wizard, and Proud Member of Relavare<img src="http://home.attbi.com/~denu5/sig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showPrevMessage?topicID=26.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showNextMessage?topicID=26.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=17><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.emailToFriend?topicID=26.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.threadControl?topicID=26.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm14.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationf